BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lYl6PhRpb8rbVGuoDIP42
SUMMARY:Journaling the Garden
DTSTAMP:20260205T082823Z
DTSTART:20260207T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Nature journaling at the Bellevue Botanical Garden is a wonderf
	ul way to connect with the environment through curiosity and observation o
	f the natural world. This free adult program will help guide your practice
	 whether you are just starting out or are an experienced journaler. In thi
	s warm and welcoming environment\, you will be encouraged to experiment an
	d find your voice. In each session we will gather for introductions and br
	ief guidance\, and then head out into Garden to journal and come back toge
	ther to share experiences.   \n\nPlease bring a dedicated journal and some
	thing to write with. We will meet at 9am the first Saturday of January-Nov
	ember 2026. Registration is recommended but not required. REGISTER HERE. \
	n\nThis free adult program is facilitated by Anne Dziok\, Adult Education 
	Program Manager. Anne is a practicing multi-media artist who shows her wor
	k regionally.    \n\nEmail us with questions.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/176
	58183/2026-02-07T00
LOCATION:Sharp Cabin\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tn1KMPV1RGKRGAuytnr7I
SUMMARY:CL 102: Portable Lighting
DTSTAMP:20260205T082823Z
DTSTART:20260207T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:If you're interested in running and hosting shows in unconventi
	onal locations\, this is the class for you! In this interactive 2-hour wor
	kshop\, students will learn the in’s and out’s of installing and programmi
	ng lights for live events outside of the venue! Participants will explore 
	areas such as installing light trees\, cable management\, programming ligh
	ts\, light design and placement\, and more. This class is great for those 
	who are interested in improving their concert lighting skills\, especially
	 for DIY shows or outdoor spaces.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/cl-102-portable-lighting/
	17682999/2026-02-07T00
LOCATION:Book-It Repertory Theatre\, 305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
